'1998, when Hema-Quebec started their work, almost 38% of people had confidence in the blood conservation system in Quebec, recalls Dr. Décary.
The situation was disturbing.
Through the enormous efforts to improve the safety of the blood conserve and through the work on this area over the following years, we have gained the trust of the public,” she says, before she proudly emphasizes that at the beginning of 2008 now almost 94% of the population of Quebec had trust in Hema-Quebec.
However, Dr. Decary keeps in mind that ‘confidence is something extremely fragile’.
Since its founding on 28 September 1998, Hema-Quebec has been acting according to the principle of caution.
At this time we experienced the appearance of numerous cases of human form of cattle disgrace in Europe, a new type of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease, this woman, who has been leading since its foundation in 1998.
